# Token Efficiency

## Before acting
- One targeted grep/search beats reading whole files or launching explore subagents.
- Read only files you will edit or that define the exact API/symbol you need.
- Large files: use offset/limit; never read the full file unless required.
- Do not re-read a file already in context this session.

## Implementation
- Smallest correct diff. No drive-by refactors, comments, or formatting churn.
- Match surrounding code style; do not invent new abstractions for one-offs.
- No tests, docs, or `.md` files unless explicitly requested.
- No todo lists for single-step or ≤3-step tasks.
- No Task/explore subagents unless the change spans many unknown modules.

## Tools
- Batch independent tool calls in one turn.
- Skip `git status/diff/log` unless committing or opening a PR.
- Skip lint runs unless you edited code and need to verify a fix.
- Prefer `Grep` over `SemanticSearch` when you know the symbol/path.

## Responses
- Be brief. No restating the task, no long summaries, no follow-up bait.
- Do not paste large code blocks — cite changed regions only when helpful.
- One sentence status while working; final answer = what changed + how to verify.
